      • allowExternalParties

        public static boolean allowExternalParties
        Opens the bungeecord messaging channel and
        automatically puts players joined after a
        Bungeecord-Party-Message containing their names
        into their own team. Kicks them if there's not enough room

      • customReconnectSystem

        public static boolean customReconnectSystem
        If the gamemode has a custom reconnect system.
        The default reconnect system will just respawn the player as a spectator.
        This might make for a bad experience in games like bedwars, but is necessary in games like survival games and sky wars.

      • customVotingSystem

        public static boolean customVotingSystem
        If the gamemode has a custom voting system.
        The default voting system will go through the map directory and make a vote for a random 5 of the maps listed there.

      • noTeamSpawns

        public static boolean noTeamSpawns
        Whether players in a team will spawn on the same spot or if they will be treated like individual players.

      • customRespawnSystem

        public static boolean customRespawnSystem
        If the gamemode has a custom respawn system.
        The default respawn system will always just set the player as a spectator.
        This doesn't work with games like bedwars, but is perfectly acceptable for games like survival games and sky wars.

        location - The location that should be modified (e.g. x: 5.291, y: 2.41, z: -2.744, yaw: 98.512, pitch: 14.213)
        Returns:

      • cleanMaps

        public static void cleanMaps()
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Goes through all maps in the map directory given in the configuration and:
        • Goes through all chunks in a 2048x2048 square around 0:0 and deletes the items/monsters
        • Applies all game rules from the mapGameRules map
        • Sets the weather to mapWeather
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
